A giant crane broke free from a skyscraper, crashing into residential buildings on Manhattan's East Side, resulting in at least two deaths.
Witnesses described the horrifying scene as the crane headed towards their windows.
A rescue operation was underway to save those trapped in the rubble.
Mayor Bloomberg confirmed four fatalities and multiple injuries, attributing the accident to safety concerns raised by residents and construction workers.
The incident highlighted the dangers of construction in the city, prompting a thorough investigation into the cause of the crane's detachment.
